  "title": "Associate Director, Equipment and Engineering",
  "description": "<p><strong>Main Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>•\tManage the technical modification team at the Singapore site, coordinate work and communication within the team, and enhance the technical and management skills of team members.</p><p>•\tDevelop and ensure the achievement of the annual technical modification plan, goals, and budget for the department.</p><p>•\tFormulate FAT (Factory Acceptance Testing) plans for equipment at the Singapore plant, organize and control the quality of FAT implementation, and approve FAT results.</p><p>•\tParticipate in the installation, commissioning, and acceptance of ongoing projects at the Singapore plant, ensuring smooth project delivery.</p><p>•\tPrepare for production readiness in equipment maintenance and technical modification, ensuring timely project delivery and smooth production processes.</p><p>•\tManage factory equipment and technical modifications, establish relevant technical standards, and ensure equipment remains in good condition to meet operational needs and comply with national and company requirements.</p><p>•\tContinuously optimize and improve the status, operability, safety, and reliability of production equipment to ensure product quality and site safety, and improve production efficiency.</p><p>•\tEstablish and optimize related operational processes, provide training, and ensure strict adherence to these processes.</p><p>•\tReview equipment change requests and assess quality and safety impacts.</p><p>•\tLead research and promotion of new technologies and processes in equipment and engineering projects, and approve technical documents such as design changes and engineering work orders.</p><p>•\tIncorporate technical and best practices from the Changzhou and Taixing sites in China into the Singapore plant.</p><p>•\tAssist the head of the equipment engineering department with daily management tasks.</p><p></p><p><strong>Competencies:</strong></p><p>•\tBachelor's degree or higher.</p><p>•\tMajor in Mechanical, Electrical, or Chemical Automation, or related fields.</p><p>•\tOver fifteen years of engineering maintenance and over five years of project team management experience in pharmaceutical or chemical industries.</p><p>•\tStrong coordination and communication skills.</p><p>•\tExcellent problem-solving and analytical abilities.</p><p>•\tProficient in reading and writing in both English and Chinese, capable of fluent technical communication with both the local Singapore team and the technical team in China.</p><p>•\tProficient in using MS Office software.</p><p></p>",
